  "texts": [
    "The validation process was performed using 20% of the training data.",
    "For the segmentation task, all the images were resized to 256 × 256 pixels.",
    "The first encoder, based on the efficientNetV2-L backbone, was used with pre-trained ImageNet [47] weights, and the second encoder, based on MSA, was trained from scratch.",
    "Various combinations of learning rates, batch sizes, and epochs were examined.",
    "The best results were achieved using the Adam [51] optimizer (4) Precision = TP TP + FP (5) Recall = TP TP + FN (6) Specifity = TN TN + FP (7) Sensitivity = TP TP + FP(8) F 1 -score = 2 × Precision × Recall Precision + Recall (9) DC = 2 × TP 2 × TP + FP + FN (10) IoU = TP TP + FP + FNwith an initial learning rate of 1e -4, β1 = 0.9, β2 = 0.999 and 1e -7, training for 200 epochs with a batch size of eight, and early stopping."
  ],
